    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-18T17:04:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-18T17:04:00-05:00" n="387"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/2–1853: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d387fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_PARSONSJG1"
                            >Parsons</persName> and cleared with <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1"
                            >Bruce</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MACARTHURDII1"
                            >MacArthur</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_BONBRIGHTJCHJ1"
                            >Bonbright</persName>. Sent also to Rome, Brussels, The Hague,
                        Luxembourg, Bonn and repeated to London and Strasbourg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-18T17:04:00-05:00"
                            >February 18, 1953—5:04 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4467. Sent Paris for <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_SRE1">SRE</gloss>.</p>
                <p>The President is announcing later today that at his request Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">David Bruce</persName> will leave for Europe next
                    week to serve as US Observer to Interim Comite of <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss> and US Rep to <gloss target="#t_CSC1">CSC</gloss> as well as to
                    follow work looking to creation of <gloss target="#t_EPC1">EPC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> plans reside Paris as
                        <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> will require major part of his time for
                    present but he will visit Luxembourg as required. Dept assumes Ambs and <gloss
                        target="#t_HICOG1">HICOG</gloss> will continue follow six country
                    developments closely but that it will be useful for Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> visit other capitals and Strasbourg
                    from time to time.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> will use personnel
                    currently working on various aspects <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>, <gloss
                        target="#t_CSC1">CSC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_EPC1">EPC</gloss> in
                    accordance with arrangements to be made after his arrival in Paris. In carrying
                    out his duties he will report directly to SecState.</p>
                <p>Guidance to media will follow but obviously US desires obtain maximum
                    psychological impact from this step which is clearest indication we could give
                    of our close support for and belief in six country efforts towards
                    unification.</p>
                <p>It will be recalled that on Aug. 27, 1952 <gloss target="#t_SRE1">SRE</gloss>
                    Press Release reported appointment of Acting US Rep pending more definitive
                    arrangements and designation of US rep to <gloss target="#t_CSC1">CSC</gloss>.
                    Dept expects that assignment of responsibility to Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> for six country developments will
                    serve to consolidate and strengthen our relations with their organizations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
